Create Another EC2 instance.

        Name: MavenAgent2
        Machine Type: t2-small
        Security Group: MaventAgent1-sg 
            Allow ssh from your system IP OR anywhere
            allow ssh from Jenkins server - security group. 


2. Login to MavenAgent2 EC2 instance. 
        ssh -i <Key-pair.pem> ubuntu@<Public-IP-MaventAgent2>

        Dependencies 
            1. Git is preinstalled = "git --version"
            2. JDK needs to be installed - JDK 21 
                    java --version
                    sudo -i 
                    apt update && apt install openjdk-21-jdk -y 
                    java --version

Need to create a directory to let jenkins install the agent tools and workspace
                    mkdir /opt/jenkins 

                    id ubuntu 

                    chown ubuntu:ubuntu /opt/jenkins 

                    ls -ld /opt/jenkins 

            3. MAVEN needs to be installed.(install it through Jenkins Master)



3. keep the key-pair ready 

        cat <key-pair.pem>

4. Now head over to jenkins 

        Manage Jenkins --> Nodes --> new nodes

            (a) Give node a name
            (b) Number of executors (parallel jobs that can be executed at one time)
            (c) Labels - MAVENBUILDER1 
            (d) Usage - Only build jobs with Label expression matching this node
            (e) Launch Method - Launch agent via ssh
                    (i) Give Agents private IP (Master and Agent both are in same network)
                    (ii) Credentials - add - Global Settings - SSH username with Private Key
                    (iii) host key verification strategy - non verifying verification strategy 
